
Installing MVP on OSX

1)

Install MacPorts https://trac.macports.org/wiki/InstallingMacPorts#RequirementsfortheMacPortsshellenvironment
    Don’t forget to add /opt/local/bin to your path in ~/.bashrc!
    Ensure you have the latest version: sudo port -v selfupdate
Install VW deps
    sudo port –v install qt4-mac boost proj gdal git-core protobuf-cpp zmq
Install additional MVP deps
    sudo port -v install cmake [octave-devel] [google-test]

2)

Check out my ‘mvp’ VW branch
    git clone git://github.com/khusmann/visionworkbench.git VisionWorkbench
    cd VisionWorkbench
    git checkout -b mvp origin/mvp
Edit/create config.options
    #! /bin/sh
    # Compile options
    #ENABLE_CCACHE=yes
    ENABLE_DEBUG=yes
    ENABLE_OPTIMIZE=yes

    # This is where vw will be installed.
    PREFIX=`pwd`/build

    # Specific modules to enable
    ENABLE_MODULE_PLATE=yes
    ENABLE_MODULE_GUI=yes
    #ENABLE_MODULE_TOOLS=no
Configure VW, verify that modules PLATE and GUI will be compiled:
    ./autogen && ./configure
Compile and install VW
    make -j4 && make install

3)

Check out the MVP
    git clone ssh://<user>@m.arc.nasa.gov/home/khusmann/MultipleViewPipeline.git
Configure the MVP
    cd MultipleViewPipeline
    mkdir build
    export VW_ROOT=<path_to_vw_build_dir>
    ccmake ..
    [Press 'c' to configure]
    [Select option 'BINARY_DIR_INSTALL']
    [Optionally select option 'BUILD_TESTS']
    [Press 'c' to reconfigure]
    [Press 'g' to generate]
Compile and install the MVP
    make -j4 && make install
Test the MVP
    cd MultipleViewPipeline/examples/synth
    ../../build/usr/bin/mvp
    ../../build/usr/bin/mvp --use-octave true
